001package io.cyborgcode.roa.ui.util;
002
003/**
004 * Represents an operation that accepts two input arguments and performs an action without returning a result.
005 *
006 * <p>This is a functional interface, meaning it can be used as the target for lambda expressions and method references.
007 * Similar to {@link java.util.function.BiConsumer}, it allows defining custom two-parameter operations.
008 *
009 * <p>The first input argument, {@code T}, represents the primary entity on which the operation is performed.
010 * The second input argument, {@code U}, provides additional data or context necessary for the operation.
011 *
012 * @author Cyborg Code Syndicate ğŸ’ğŸ‘¨ğŸ’»
013 */
014@FunctionalInterface
015public interface BiConsumer<T, U> {
016
017   /**
018    * Performs the defined operation on the given arguments.
019    *
020    * @param t the first input argument
021    * @param u the second input argument
022    */
023   void accept(T t, U u);
024}
